1
00:00:00,430 --> 00:00:04,684
(crowd cheering)

2
00:00:06,812 --> 00:00:08,188
Whoa!
Wow...

3
00:00:16,154 --> 00:00:17,656
Whoa!

4
00:00:17,739 --> 00:00:18,740
Awesome!

5
00:00:26,665 --> 00:00:28,083
What!
Nice one!

6
00:00:33,380 --> 00:00:34,381
Aah!

7
00:00:35,924 --> 00:00:37,425
Huh?
Hyah!

8
00:00:37,509 --> 00:00:40,804
Ohh!

9
00:00:40,887 --> 00:00:42,055
Damn it!

10
00:00:42,430 --> 00:00:48,436
♪~

11
00:00:55,402 --> 00:00:58,989
Slicing through the black shadows
and the darkness, the light of deduction.

12
00:00:59,072 --> 00:01:02,909
Sanada's wild, all-out shot...
turning into an unexpected case?

13
00:01:02,993 --> 00:01:04,369
He sees the one and only truth.

14
00:01:04,452 --> 00:01:06,496
A child in appearance, with the mind of an adult.

15
00:01:06,580 --> 00:01:08,790
His name is... Detective Conan!

16
00:01:30,997 --> 00:01:37,003
~♪

17
00:02:40,953 --> 00:02:46,653
"Promise with the J-Leaguer"

18
00:02:46,653 --> 00:02:47,653
Aww...

19
00:02:48,940 --> 00:02:51,859
Big Osaka just can't get a goal, huh.

20
00:02:52,568 --> 00:02:54,237
What? Weren't you three...

21
00:02:54,320 --> 00:02:56,364
anti-Big in the first place?

22
00:02:56,447 --> 00:03:00,660
Oh, no, no. We're just
Spirits fans, that's all...

23
00:03:00,743 --> 00:03:02,787
But since we got to know

24
00:03:02,870 --> 00:03:05,414
Sanada at the soccer clinic...

25
00:03:05,498 --> 00:03:09,252
the three of us decided we'd at least
cheer for Sanada, right?

26
00:03:09,335 --> 00:03:10,795
And yet...

27
00:03:10,878 --> 00:03:14,799
Big Osaka's just no good
without Higo, huh.

28
00:03:14,882 --> 00:03:16,551
Can't be helped.

29
00:03:16,634 --> 00:03:19,178
Higo's playing in the World Cup,

30
00:03:19,262 --> 00:03:21,806
so he can't take part in this tournament.

31
00:03:22,098 --> 00:03:23,683
Alongside Hide, he's

32
00:03:23,766 --> 00:03:26,561
one of Japan's top strikers, after all.

33
00:03:26,644 --> 00:03:30,439
So that's why Sanada's
playing in Higo's place.

34
00:03:30,523 --> 00:03:33,526
Sanada's just Higo's backup.

35
00:03:33,609 --> 00:03:35,236
Though, to us...

36
00:03:35,319 --> 00:03:38,614
Hey! I'm not a backup!

37
00:03:38,990 --> 00:03:42,243
I'm a super sub. Remember that.

38
00:03:42,535 --> 00:03:44,370
...is what he told us, anyway.

39
00:03:44,453 --> 00:03:45,913
(all laughing)

40
00:03:45,997 --> 00:03:48,875
But that shot just now
was so close, huh.

41
00:03:48,958 --> 00:03:51,752
He kicked it with his right foot.

42
00:03:51,836 --> 00:03:53,462
He was trying to get past

43
00:03:53,546 --> 00:03:55,631
the defender's block, I'd guess.

44
00:03:55,715 --> 00:03:57,717
The aim was good, I thought.

45
00:03:57,800 --> 00:03:59,760
Was it though?
Huh?

46
00:04:00,052 --> 00:04:03,931
At that timing, there was no need
to cut back with a feint.

47
00:04:04,015 --> 00:04:07,268
If he'd just shot with his left foot,
aiming for the left of the goal...

48
00:04:07,351 --> 00:04:09,478
it would've gone in for sure.

49
00:04:11,272 --> 00:04:13,482
Then why would he bother...

50
00:04:13,816 --> 00:04:16,903
I don't know, but
it was the same earlier too.

51
00:04:16,986 --> 00:04:18,279
Earlier?

52
00:04:18,362 --> 00:04:21,449
You know, that perfect cross

53
00:04:21,532 --> 00:04:23,492
to Sanada when he dove in front of the goal?

54
00:04:24,535 --> 00:04:27,788
I figured he'd take a volley
with his left foot, but...

55
00:04:31,125 --> 00:04:32,501
(crowd booing)

56
00:04:32,585 --> 00:04:35,713
Hmm... come to think of it,
he shot with his right foot

57
00:04:35,796 --> 00:04:38,966
and sent it way over the crossbar.

58
00:04:39,050 --> 00:04:41,260
That time too, I wondered

59
00:04:41,344 --> 00:04:44,305
why he'd bother shooting
with his right foot,

60
00:04:44,388 --> 00:04:46,098
which isn't his dominant one.

61
00:04:46,349 --> 00:04:48,434
Maybe he was trying to show the coach

62
00:04:48,517 --> 00:04:51,354
that he can shoot
with his right foot too?

63
00:04:51,437 --> 00:04:53,981
Though it seems to be backfiring.

64
00:04:54,065 --> 00:04:55,816
And there's one more thing.

65
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:58,945
This has been bugging me too...

66
00:04:59,028 --> 00:05:02,365
Every now and then, Sanada
looks over at the stands...

67
00:05:02,448 --> 00:05:03,491
Ah, there it is again.

68
00:05:06,577 --> 00:05:08,913
See? He's looking over that way.

69
00:05:08,996 --> 00:05:10,831
I wonder who he's looking at.

70
00:05:10,915 --> 00:05:14,293
Who knows. From here
I can't tell, but...

71
00:05:14,377 --> 00:05:16,796
he's definitely watching someone.

72
00:05:18,047 --> 00:05:21,008
Don't tell me... someone's threatening him,

73
00:05:21,092 --> 00:05:22,885
and he's missing shots on purpose?

74
00:05:23,094 --> 00:05:24,595
Huh?
Hm?

75
00:05:25,012 --> 00:05:27,431
...Just kidding. No way that's it.

76
00:05:27,682 --> 00:05:29,517
Why would you think that?

77
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:31,060
Huh?
Was there

78
00:05:31,143 --> 00:05:33,104
a similar case before, maybe?

79
00:05:33,187 --> 00:05:35,773
Oh, no. Nothing like that.

80
00:05:35,856 --> 00:05:38,442
Sorry. I'm overthinking it.

81
00:05:38,526 --> 00:05:40,820
Let's just watch the game.
Mm...

82
00:05:44,073 --> 00:05:48,160
(Still, Sanada's play
is clearly off.)

83
00:05:48,244 --> 00:05:50,037
(Something's definitely going on.)

84
00:05:50,705 --> 00:05:51,831
Ayumi-chan.
Hm?

85
00:05:51,914 --> 00:05:53,708
Genta-kun.
Hm?

86
00:05:53,791 --> 00:05:58,129
Conan-kun's deduction...
maybe it's actually right.

87
00:05:58,212 --> 00:06:00,464
You mean Sanada's being threatened

88
00:06:00,548 --> 00:06:02,508
and missing shots on purpose?

89
00:06:02,591 --> 00:06:03,592
Yes.

90
00:06:04,218 --> 00:06:08,055
Conan-kun must have a reason
for thinking so.

91
00:06:08,472 --> 00:06:10,975
He's just hiding it from us.

92
00:06:11,058 --> 00:06:12,309
If that's true...

93
00:06:12,393 --> 00:06:15,271
let's save that guy ourselves!

94
00:06:15,354 --> 00:06:16,355
Yes.

95
00:06:16,939 --> 00:06:18,232
Conan-kun.
Hm?

96
00:06:18,566 --> 00:06:21,277
We're gonna run to the restroom for a bit.

97
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:23,612
Oh, okay. Hm?

98
00:06:31,162 --> 00:06:33,789
Ah... hey, that guy.

99
00:06:34,290 --> 00:06:36,500
He looks really suspicious.

100
00:06:36,584 --> 00:06:39,587
Yeah. Let's get closer
and take a look.

101
00:06:40,171 --> 00:06:42,840
Go, Sanada-kun!

102
00:06:42,923 --> 00:06:44,550
Let's go, Sanada!

103
00:06:49,638 --> 00:06:50,806
Clear it! Push the line up!

104
00:06:51,474 --> 00:06:52,641
Won't go in...

105
00:06:52,725 --> 00:06:54,435
Ohh...
Sanada-kun!

106
00:06:54,518 --> 00:06:55,603
Don't mind, don't mind.

107
00:06:58,189 --> 00:06:59,690
That old guy...

108
00:06:59,774 --> 00:07:02,902
He seems to be watching Sanada

109
00:07:02,985 --> 00:07:05,279
and that lady cheering for Sanada.

110
00:07:05,362 --> 00:07:06,572
Suspicious, huh.

111
00:07:09,909 --> 00:07:11,744
If it isn't Conan-kun!
Hm?

112
00:07:11,827 --> 00:07:13,662
Oh, Kaoru-san.

113
00:07:14,163 --> 00:07:15,581
Watching the game today

114
00:07:15,664 --> 00:07:17,541
with your girlfriend?

115
00:07:17,625 --> 00:07:19,335
Huh? Uh, no...

116
00:07:19,418 --> 00:07:20,503
I'm not.

117
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:23,839
Oh, is that so?
My apologies, then.

118
00:07:24,340 --> 00:07:26,634
You're not working today, right, Kaoru-san?

119
00:07:26,717 --> 00:07:29,136
You're not wearing a press bib.

120
00:07:29,470 --> 00:07:31,764
That's right. I'm off today.

121
00:07:31,847 --> 00:07:35,976
That scoop photo got me
back into the social affairs desk.

122
00:07:36,435 --> 00:07:41,440
And after that whole string of cases,
I got personally interested in Sanada Takahiro...

123
00:07:41,857 --> 00:07:43,192
Hyah!

124
00:07:43,526 --> 00:07:45,611
So I'm still following him.

125
00:07:45,694 --> 00:07:47,696
Hmm. Hey.

126
00:07:47,780 --> 00:07:50,783
Doesn't Sanada seem
a little off today?

127
00:07:50,866 --> 00:07:54,453
Yeah. He's not like
his usual self.

128
00:07:54,537 --> 00:07:58,624
Two days ago, when Big was on their
Tokyo road trip, I went to the field

129
00:07:58,707 --> 00:08:01,168
near the Nishishiba Hotel,
where they always stay,

130
00:08:01,252 --> 00:08:04,839
and got photos of Sanada
doing his early-morning solo practice.

131
00:08:04,922 --> 00:08:08,467
Back then, was he practicing
shots with his right foot?

132
00:08:08,551 --> 00:08:12,263
No. He was practicing PKs,

133
00:08:12,346 --> 00:08:15,182
but he kicked every one
with his left foot.

134
00:08:15,266 --> 00:08:17,726
And with a hard, straight shot,

135
00:08:17,810 --> 00:08:20,521
aiming for the upper left corner of the goal.

136
00:08:20,604 --> 00:08:24,275
He kept drilling that one course
over and over.

137
00:08:24,775 --> 00:08:29,363
(Just as I thought.
So why is he using his right foot today...)

138
00:08:34,201 --> 00:08:36,370
Ah! So close.

139
00:08:37,079 --> 00:08:40,541
...Anyway, this field
brings back memories.

140
00:08:40,624 --> 00:08:42,626
What, you've been here before?

141
00:08:42,710 --> 00:08:45,337
Yeah. Nishishiba Sports Park.

142
00:08:45,421 --> 00:08:48,883
There was a soccer tournament here
back in middle school.

143
00:08:49,258 --> 00:08:51,385
A few days before that tournament,

144
00:08:52,052 --> 00:08:56,182
I wanted to check the turf and stuff,
so I was kicking a ball around alone.

145
00:08:56,849 --> 00:08:59,101
At the end, I tried a few PKs too.

146
00:08:59,185 --> 00:09:00,895
Just like Sanada...

147
00:09:01,312 --> 00:09:05,524
I aimed for the upper left corner
with a hard, straight ball.

148
00:09:06,901 --> 00:09:09,153
But I put too much into it...

149
00:09:12,573 --> 00:09:15,910
Heh. So the super
high-school-level soccer kid

150
00:09:15,993 --> 00:09:18,829
missed a PK with no keeper.

151
00:09:18,913 --> 00:09:20,581
I said it was in middle school!

152
00:09:20,664 --> 00:09:22,875
Hmm.
Huh? Middle school?

153
00:09:22,958 --> 00:09:24,710
Uh... what?

154
00:09:24,793 --> 00:09:27,463
You just said "in middle school."

155
00:09:27,838 --> 00:09:31,133
Ah, no. It's a story
about a guy I know...

156
00:09:31,217 --> 00:09:32,676
Hmm.

157
00:09:33,802 --> 00:09:35,930
(crowd cheering)

158
00:09:36,013 --> 00:09:39,225
Sanada-kun, you can do it!

159
00:09:40,517 --> 00:09:44,146
Huh? What's that?
That thing by his knee...

160
00:09:46,148 --> 00:09:49,193
What is that? Looks like
a black tube...

161
00:09:49,276 --> 00:09:51,153
Ah, it's a gun!
Huh?

162
00:09:51,237 --> 00:09:53,364
Could that be a gun barrel...

163
00:09:53,447 --> 00:09:56,158
Is a gun barrel
really that thick?

164
00:09:56,825 --> 00:09:58,160
It's a silencer.

165
00:09:58,244 --> 00:10:00,955
A device you attach to a gun
so the sound can't be heard.

166
00:10:01,372 --> 00:10:03,749
You see them a lot
in spy movies.

167
00:10:05,334 --> 00:10:07,169
Here's the truth.

168
00:10:07,253 --> 00:10:10,381
That woman cheering
for Sanada...

169
00:10:10,464 --> 00:10:12,341
is Sanada's girlfriend,

170
00:10:12,424 --> 00:10:15,844
and he's being threatened that if he
doesn't want her killed,

171
00:10:15,928 --> 00:10:18,430
he has to miss his shots.

172
00:10:18,931 --> 00:10:22,935
That's why he's deliberately shooting
with his right foot, not his dominant one!

173
00:10:23,018 --> 00:10:25,896
Whaat?
Wh... what do we do, Mitsuhiko?

174
00:10:25,980 --> 00:10:27,940
Hmm... hm?

175
00:10:29,441 --> 00:10:31,860
Let's tell a security guard.
(crowd cheering)

176
00:10:35,072 --> 00:10:36,907
Hmph!
Ah...

177
00:10:37,324 --> 00:10:40,995
(crowd cheering)

178
00:10:41,078 --> 00:10:42,496
Good job, Takahiro.

179
00:10:42,579 --> 00:10:44,873
Ah! Oh no.

180
00:10:44,957 --> 00:10:46,917
(crowd cheering)

181
00:10:47,001 --> 00:10:48,419
Kyaa!

182
00:10:49,086 --> 00:10:50,212
This is bad!

183
00:10:50,296 --> 00:10:51,880
He scored!

184
00:10:54,550 --> 00:10:56,927
Ah! Watch out!
Stop!

185
00:10:57,011 --> 00:10:59,013
Whoa! What the... who are you kids?

186
00:10:59,722 --> 00:11:00,723
Let go!

187
00:11:00,806 --> 00:11:02,016
We won't let go!

188
00:11:02,099 --> 00:11:03,976
You're threatening Sanada, aren't you?

189
00:11:04,059 --> 00:11:06,061
Ayumi-chan, get a guard, quick!

190
00:11:06,687 --> 00:11:10,316
Hey, you two.
It doesn't seem to be a gun.

191
00:11:12,359 --> 00:11:13,360
Huh?

192
00:11:13,652 --> 00:11:15,279
Hey, you kids.

193
00:11:16,655 --> 00:11:18,824
Hey, let go.

194
00:11:18,907 --> 00:11:21,076
What are you doing, you guys?

195
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:25,080
We were sure it was
a gun silencer...

196
00:11:25,372 --> 00:11:29,501
That's a video camera.
A hidden one, at that.

197
00:11:29,585 --> 00:11:33,505
Wh... what are you talking about?
I don't know anything. Ah...

198
00:11:33,589 --> 00:11:36,842
Ah! That man... he's Yuki's stalker.

199
00:11:37,509 --> 00:11:39,011
Ohh...

200
00:11:41,430 --> 00:11:45,309
Those women weren't
Sanada's girlfriends...

201
00:11:45,392 --> 00:11:47,853
they were just fans, it seems.

202
00:11:47,936 --> 00:11:49,355
Geez. Good thing

203
00:11:49,438 --> 00:11:51,732
that was a video camera.

204
00:11:51,815 --> 00:11:53,484
If it'd been a real gun,

205
00:11:53,567 --> 00:11:55,903
who knows what
might've happened to you.

206
00:11:55,986 --> 00:11:59,031
But thanks to that,
I got some interesting photos.

207
00:11:59,114 --> 00:12:00,157
Thanks.

208
00:12:00,240 --> 00:12:02,743
As a thank-you, I'll buy you
something at the stand.

209
00:12:02,826 --> 00:12:04,578
It's halftime anyway.

210
00:12:04,661 --> 00:12:07,456
Yay! Haha...

211
00:12:07,539 --> 00:12:08,582
Geez.

212
00:12:08,665 --> 00:12:10,584
Don't "geez" me, okay?

213
00:12:10,667 --> 00:12:13,128
You're the one who said all that,
so those kids...

214
00:12:13,212 --> 00:12:15,255
Well, true enough, I guess.

215
00:12:15,339 --> 00:12:19,176
But there's no doubt
something's going on with Sanada.

216
00:12:19,259 --> 00:12:20,344
Ah...

217
00:12:24,765 --> 00:12:27,101
Ah... hmph.

218
00:12:30,104 --> 00:12:31,188
I'm gonna hit the restroom.

219
00:12:31,271 --> 00:12:33,607
You okay? Want me to come with you?
- Fukazawa Shingo (40), convenience store owner.
- Watanabe Kou (10) Nishishiba primary school 4th grader.

220
00:12:33,690 --> 00:12:35,275
I'm fine.

221
00:12:43,117 --> 00:12:45,202
(So he was watching that kid.)

222
00:14:46,236 --> 00:14:48,196
Hm?
Ah...

223
00:14:57,580 --> 00:15:00,291
Hey, mister.
Hm... huh?

224
00:15:00,375 --> 00:15:03,253
What happened to
that kid's right foot?

225
00:15:03,336 --> 00:15:06,256
Oh, he fell off his bike
and twisted it.

226
00:15:06,339 --> 00:15:09,384
Hmm. Are you
that kid's dad?

227
00:15:09,467 --> 00:15:11,511
Ah... no, I'm not.

228
00:15:11,594 --> 00:15:14,889
You don't look like
his soccer club coach either, but...

229
00:15:15,557 --> 00:15:18,476
Is that kid friends with Sanada?

230
00:15:18,810 --> 00:15:20,061
Why do you ask?

231
00:15:20,145 --> 00:15:23,982
Because Sanada was
sending him some kind of signal.

232
00:15:27,318 --> 00:15:30,572
Hey, does that kid
falling off his bike

233
00:15:30,655 --> 00:15:33,491
have something to do
with Sanada?

234
00:15:34,117 --> 00:15:35,952
Why would you think that?

235
00:15:36,035 --> 00:15:38,288
When Sanada comes to Tokyo,

236
00:15:38,371 --> 00:15:42,000
the field where he always does
his solo practice is in Nishishiba.

237
00:15:42,083 --> 00:15:45,003
And it was written
on that kid's jacket too.

238
00:15:45,462 --> 00:15:48,006
"Nishishiba Soccer Club."

239
00:15:49,257 --> 00:15:50,467
(sigh)

240
00:15:52,093 --> 00:15:55,013
I run a convenience store
in Nishishiba,

241
00:15:55,472 --> 00:15:59,809
and the other morning I was taking
a walk through the nearby sports park...

242
00:16:00,435 --> 00:16:01,978
(ball being kicked)
Hm?

243
00:16:02,812 --> 00:16:04,564
(brakes screeching)

244
00:16:04,647 --> 00:16:06,816
(crash)
Ah!

245
00:16:08,067 --> 00:16:10,445
Ngh...
Whoa?

246
00:16:11,279 --> 00:16:13,072
Ugh...

247
00:16:15,325 --> 00:16:17,994
You okay? I...
My leg...

248
00:16:18,077 --> 00:16:21,498
Ah, sorry, sorry!
I was practicing PKs

249
00:16:21,581 --> 00:16:24,667
and the ball flew over the goal...
ah.

250
00:16:24,918 --> 00:16:26,377
Aah...

251
00:16:26,461 --> 00:16:28,463
Did you get hurt?

252
00:16:29,130 --> 00:16:30,715
So I took him to

253
00:16:30,798 --> 00:16:33,510
a nearby hospital I knew...

254
00:16:34,093 --> 00:16:36,888
With this leg, I can't
play in the game.

255
00:16:37,472 --> 00:16:41,184
It's fine. Give it ten days
and you'll be running again.

256
00:16:41,518 --> 00:16:43,269
But I won't be able to shoot.

257
00:16:43,520 --> 00:16:47,148
That's not true. And if you
can't shoot with your right,

258
00:16:47,232 --> 00:16:49,150
just shoot with your left.

259
00:16:50,443 --> 00:16:51,903
Then, Sanada-san,

260
00:16:51,986 --> 00:16:54,531
can you shoot with your right,
even though it's not your dominant foot?

261
00:16:54,822 --> 00:16:59,410
Uh... of course I can!
I'm a J-Leaguer, after all.

262
00:16:59,494 --> 00:17:01,287
My right's perfect too.

263
00:17:01,579 --> 00:17:05,333
Then in your next game,
score a goal with your right foot.

264
00:17:05,416 --> 00:17:07,210
If you do, I'll work hard too.

265
00:17:07,293 --> 00:17:08,461
Whaat?

266
00:17:09,295 --> 00:17:11,506
(So Sanada...)

267
00:17:12,340 --> 00:17:13,925
Later on, Sanada

268
00:17:14,008 --> 00:17:16,844
sent us tickets for today's game.

269
00:17:16,928 --> 00:17:21,349
But Ko's parents were busy,
so I came in their place.

270
00:17:22,976 --> 00:17:24,394
Thanks, mister.

271
00:17:24,477 --> 00:17:26,104
(whistle)

272
00:17:28,064 --> 00:17:29,232
Unbelievable.

273
00:17:29,649 --> 00:17:32,735
No matter how guilty he felt
about injuring the kid,

274
00:17:32,819 --> 00:17:36,573
what J-Leaguer makes
such a ridiculous promise?

275
00:17:36,656 --> 00:17:40,118
Well, that's just
so very Sanada...

276
00:17:40,201 --> 00:17:42,579
Maybe it's what's good about him?

277
00:17:42,996 --> 00:17:45,748
I wanna see Sanada score
in the second half too.

278
00:17:45,832 --> 00:17:48,876
Not some lame shot
like before.

279
00:17:48,960 --> 00:17:51,087
I want him to nail it big.

280
00:17:52,672 --> 00:17:55,133
(What bugs me more, though...)

281
00:17:55,508 --> 00:17:58,678
(phone ringing)

282
00:17:58,761 --> 00:18:02,473
Yes, Nishishiba Sports Park
management office.

283
00:18:03,433 --> 00:18:07,812
Huh? Mouri? You mean
the famous Detective Mouri?

284
00:18:17,030 --> 00:18:18,031
Hm?

285
00:18:18,531 --> 00:18:21,200
I heard the story
from Fukazawa-san.

286
00:18:21,284 --> 00:18:24,203
Cut Sanada some slack, will you?

287
00:18:24,287 --> 00:18:27,165
No way. A promise is a promise.

288
00:18:27,457 --> 00:18:30,918
But your injury isn't
Sanada's fault.

289
00:18:31,210 --> 00:18:34,505
What are you talking about?
The ball he kicked...

290
00:18:34,589 --> 00:18:35,590
Hm?

291
00:18:35,673 --> 00:18:38,426
Can you show me where
you fell off your bike?

292
00:18:38,676 --> 00:18:41,012
Huh? Oh, sure.

293
00:18:41,929 --> 00:18:43,514
Around here, I think.

294
00:18:43,890 --> 00:18:45,224
You're sure?

295
00:18:45,308 --> 00:18:49,646
Yeah. It was right after I
passed the crosswalk.

296
00:18:50,355 --> 00:18:53,191
Which direction did
the ball come flying from?

297
00:18:53,274 --> 00:18:54,859
From diagonally behind me.

298
00:18:54,942 --> 00:18:59,322
Sanada was kicking from this spot,
toward the upper left corner of the goal,

299
00:18:59,405 --> 00:19:01,908
a hard, straight ball.

300
00:19:02,116 --> 00:19:06,496
But he put too much into it,
and the ball flew way over the goal.

301
00:19:06,579 --> 00:19:09,582
If that ball flew over Fukazawa-san's head

302
00:19:09,666 --> 00:19:12,835
and out onto the road in front...

303
00:19:13,670 --> 00:19:16,631
See? A ball aimed at
the upper left of the goal

304
00:19:16,714 --> 00:19:20,176
couldn't possibly come flying
from diagonally behind

305
00:19:20,259 --> 00:19:23,054
at Ko, who'd just passed
beside the crosswalk.

306
00:19:23,137 --> 00:19:25,473
Huh? Then how...

307
00:19:25,807 --> 00:19:28,476
There's only one possibility.

308
00:19:28,559 --> 00:19:31,104
First, the ball Sanada kicked

309
00:19:31,187 --> 00:19:33,981
didn't fly over
Fukazawa-san's head...

310
00:19:34,065 --> 00:19:35,483
it hit Fukazawa-san.

311
00:19:35,983 --> 00:19:38,236
Right in the face, in fact.

312
00:19:38,319 --> 00:19:39,404
Huh?

313
00:19:39,987 --> 00:19:44,242
Fukazawa-san, those glasses
seem to be in bad shape.

314
00:19:44,826 --> 00:19:47,829
Look closely and the arm's
slightly bent...

315
00:19:48,329 --> 00:19:49,914
Didn't a ball hit them?

316
00:19:49,997 --> 00:19:52,083
No... that's not what happened.

317
00:19:52,166 --> 00:19:54,335
Ah, wait a second.

318
00:19:54,419 --> 00:19:57,880
If the ball hit Fukazawa-san
like you say,

319
00:19:57,964 --> 00:20:00,425
then how did the ball
end up reaching me...

320
00:20:00,717 --> 00:20:05,388
Right. There's no way the ball
should've reached Ko.

321
00:20:05,471 --> 00:20:08,474
Unless Fukazawa-san,
hit in the face by the ball,

322
00:20:08,558 --> 00:20:12,103
got angry and threw it
toward the street out front.

323
00:20:14,272 --> 00:20:15,773
N... no.

324
00:20:15,857 --> 00:20:18,192
I saw the ball
well before that,

325
00:20:18,276 --> 00:20:21,320
and it definitely flew
over my head.

326
00:20:21,404 --> 00:20:25,116
The course of Sanada's
kicked ball is wrong to begin with.

327
00:20:25,408 --> 00:20:27,368
Try to remember carefully.

328
00:20:27,452 --> 00:20:31,289
The ball came from the side,
not from diagonally behind, right?

329
00:20:32,790 --> 00:20:34,792
Ah... um...

330
00:20:35,543 --> 00:20:36,544
Fukazawa-san.

331
00:20:38,045 --> 00:20:40,798
Did you know there's
a security camera

332
00:20:40,882 --> 00:20:43,092
right here at that field?
Huh?

333
00:20:44,886 --> 00:20:47,972
I called the park
management office earlier

334
00:20:48,347 --> 00:20:50,933
and had them check
the footage from that day.

335
00:20:57,190 --> 00:20:58,399
Ugh...

336
00:21:13,456 --> 00:21:14,582
Damn it.

337
00:21:18,377 --> 00:21:20,546
Why would you go that far...

338
00:21:20,630 --> 00:21:24,467
It's not that I wanted to
expose your crime, Fukazawa-san.

339
00:21:24,550 --> 00:21:27,345
You're not a bad person, after all.

340
00:21:27,428 --> 00:21:30,181
I just had to bring out the truth.

341
00:21:30,264 --> 00:21:33,893
For Sanada's sake,
and for Ko's sake.

342
00:21:33,976 --> 00:21:34,977
Huh...

343
00:21:35,853 --> 00:21:39,065
It's a foul!
PK! PK!

344
00:21:43,778 --> 00:21:45,822
Nobu, it's on you.

345
00:21:47,657 --> 00:21:48,699
You got it.

346
00:21:50,284 --> 00:21:53,120
(If I kick it left-footed
on that course like in practice,

347
00:21:53,204 --> 00:21:55,164
I'll score for sure.)

348
00:21:56,082 --> 00:21:59,710
(But if I do that,
then my promise with that kid...)

349
00:22:11,889 --> 00:22:12,890
Hm?

350
00:22:16,352 --> 00:22:18,354
Ow! Ah...

351
00:22:25,027 --> 00:22:26,320
Mm.

352
00:22:26,946 --> 00:22:28,072
Ah...

353
00:22:29,740 --> 00:22:30,825
Yeah.

354
00:22:30,908 --> 00:22:32,493
Haha.

355
00:22:46,173 --> 00:22:47,383
(whistle)

356
00:23:00,980 --> 00:23:02,273
Aah...

357
00:23:02,773 --> 00:23:04,108
Aww...

358
00:23:05,902 --> 00:23:07,111
Unbelievable.

359
00:23:07,737 --> 00:23:09,614
Just another lame shot, huh.

360
00:23:09,697 --> 00:23:11,282
Damn...

361
00:23:13,910 --> 00:23:17,079
Don't mind, don't mind.
No time to sulk, man.

362
00:23:17,163 --> 00:23:18,247
Idiot.

363
00:23:18,331 --> 00:23:19,832
Don't say it yourself.

364
00:23:20,791 --> 00:23:22,126
Thanks.

365
00:23:22,460 --> 00:23:25,296
Well, that's so very Sanada.

366
00:23:26,172 --> 00:23:32,178
♪~

367
00:24:40,454 --> 00:24:45,751
~♪

368
00:24:48,587 --> 00:24:51,173
So it was the ball
you threw?

369
00:24:51,924 --> 00:24:54,385
I'm sorry I lied.

370
00:24:54,468 --> 00:24:56,971
Sanada-san. Ko.

371
00:24:57,555 --> 00:24:58,681
I'm truly sorry.

372
00:24:58,973 --> 00:25:03,394
It's okay, mister. I'm gonna
work hard in my next game.

373
00:25:05,688 --> 00:25:07,606
Mm...
Ah.

374
00:25:10,776 --> 00:25:12,611
Wh... whoa, Sanada-kun?

375
00:25:14,864 --> 00:25:17,116
I'm sorry.
Huh?

376
00:25:17,700 --> 00:25:19,952
Even if you were the one
who threw the ball,

377
00:25:20,036 --> 00:25:24,206
it doesn't change that my kick
got Ko injured.

378
00:25:24,290 --> 00:25:28,627
And on top of that, I hit you
in the face... forgive me.

379
00:25:33,132 --> 00:25:34,300
Sanada-san...

380
00:25:34,383 --> 00:25:35,426
Hm? Ah.

381
00:25:35,509 --> 00:25:38,888
(Ko laughing)

382
00:25:42,892 --> 00:25:46,395
But you'd normally
make that PK, huh.

383
00:25:47,938 --> 00:25:52,860
(rain falling)

384
00:25:53,360 --> 00:25:54,361
Heh.

385
00:25:55,029 --> 00:25:57,406
A woman's body found
near the scene from earlier?

386
00:25:57,490 --> 00:26:00,117
H... hey. Don't tell me...

387
00:26:00,618 --> 00:26:02,119
No way...

388
00:26:02,453 --> 00:26:03,913
What the heck.

389
00:26:04,121 --> 00:26:06,373
The pain finally woke me up.

390
00:26:06,749 --> 00:26:08,876
This case isn't over yet.

391
00:26:09,376 --> 00:26:11,921
Mouri-san, what do you mean
"isn't over"...

392
00:26:12,453 --> 00:26:17,753
Next Conan:
"Coincidences Come in Twos"

393
00:26:33,153 --> 00:26:35,553
Next Conan's Hint:

394
00:26:35,553 --> 00:26:37,953
"A brand new skirt"

395
00:26:37,953 --> 00:26:39,997
Reds' Makino, take it away.

396
00:26:40,081 --> 00:26:42,374
Go, Japan!
